experience.description:
Role-Process Interrelation Framework | Org Design + HR Tech + Systems Thinking

I’m currently designing and developing a strategic HR product: a Role-Process Interrelation Framework.
This no-code tool helps companies visualize dependencies between roles, responsibilities, and business processes — enabling scalable org design, clearer role definition, and improved cross-functional collaboration.

What started as a People Ops need in fast-paced environments evolved into a product mindset approach to solving structural misalignment and inefficiencies across growing teams.

Key aspects:
✅Maps workflows and ownership across teams;
✅Identifies blockers and role overlaps;
✅Promotes data-informed org decisions;
✅Supports hiring prioritization and process clarity;
✅Designed with async, remote-first teams in mind.

I built this with scale, autonomy, and clarity in mind — and I’m excited to keep iterating as I test it in real use cases.

